11/03/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski opened a two-day summit on development and co-operation among countries in South East Europe (SEE) on Thursday (10 March) in Skopje. 
He told participants that the countries in the region are on their way to becoming modern market economies, but acknowledged many challenges remain, including implementation of reforms. 
He urged regional co-operation on economic issues, security and stability. 
An estimated 150 heads of state and government, senior officials and members of the business community are participating in the forum. 
(MIA, Makfax - 10/03/05)
